rComments: I just heard that Prof. Soroko won the teaching award a bunch of us nominated her for. So well deserved! Her course was outstanding. Well designed, innovative and interesting readings on today's most important topics. She is whip-smart, so funny and actually cares about her students. Dazzling personality too. Bravo!

It's my last semester and it's not that I didn't appreciate Agata's course last year but I have a newfound appreciation for it after taking other classes. There is something special about Agata's class and the environment she cultivates. She's also very organized, clear and really connects with students. Ottawa U is not the same without her here.
I loved taking EDU 7133 with professor Soroko! Her course was immensely relevant and engaging. Despite the course being asynchronous, she was very accessible. I learned so much!

This class is incredibly well put together, relevant and interesting. The professor has this magnetic energy you just want to be around. Unfortunately EDU7133 is an asynchronous course, so make use of office hours. Agata explains things very clearly and she's a great conversationlist. I visited a couple of times and it was great to talk to her.

I started a new course this week and already there is no comparison to EDU7133. Take any class with Agata you can. Even with online learning in the pandemic she makes class engaging and I something to look forward to.

I've taken a LOT of course at Ottawa U by now because I'm at the end of the program and Education in times of crises is by far the best course in the program. It's not easy to get a good grade but the professor actually works with you and gives you feedback to help you do your best work. Really talented smart professor and interesting readings.
Amazing prof. Amazing course. Take it but her summer class has a waiting list!
